We will not add PDF or DOCX file reading to the AI chat agent. The agent
operates as a text-only Python REPL — it generates code, executes it, and
feeds text results back to the LLM. This works well for structured data
formats (TSV, CSV, XLSX) where the content is tabular and can be
manipulated programmatically.

PDF and DOCX files, however, routinely contain images (figures, diagrams,
gel images, microscopy). A user who loads a paper will inevitably ask the
LLM to interpret a figure, and the agent has no vision capability — it
cannot render pages to images or pass them to a multimodal model. The
feature would appear to work for text-heavy documents but break in a
confusing way the moment an image matters, which in scientific papers is
most of the time.

The text extraction itself is also a heavy dependency burden (mupdf WASM
at ~30MB for PDF, mammoth for DOCX) for a feature that would be
fundamentally limited. If vision-capable agentic loops are added in the
future this decision could be revisited, but for the current text-only
sandbox architecture it is not worth pursuing.

XLSX support (structured tabular data, no images) is a separate feature
that is appropriate and planned — see brainstorming/xl_file_feature.md.
